        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-02-17 16:47:08.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> (1 comment)\n > \n > > > Jim - is this going to work?\n > >\n > > as long as the environment variables make it to the JVM, it seems\n > > like this should work, yes.\n > \n > I think csits will break for components using RestServer, so\n > companion changes would need to go there unless there was a default\n > fallback option to use the parameters per comment below.\n\nIt seems like it IS backward compatible.  If the value isn't enclosed in \"${}\", then it just returns the value unchanged.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
