        "timestamp": "2020-02-17 16:55:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\n> > (1 comment)\n > >\n > > > > Jim - is this going to work?\n > > >\n > > > as long as the environment variables make it to the JVM, it\n > seems\n > > > like this should work, yes.\n > >\n > > I think csits will break for components using RestServer, so\n > > companion changes would need to go there unless there was a\n > default\n > > fallback option to use the parameters per comment below.\n > \n > It seems like it IS backward compatible.  If the value isn't\n > enclosed in \"${}\", then it just returns the value unchanged.\n\nAhh right, nice!",
